:6;--c-lg:8"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-gUQvok iVVDxu pf-209_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-cTAqQK eHolsa pf-210_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-jKTccl dCeBIC pf-212_">Red light for Cellulite vs. Laser Cellulite Treatment</span></h3><p class="sc-bBHHxi fhourC pf-213_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Technically, red light therapy is a type of laser treatment. Sometimes it’s even called LED therapy or cold laser therapy. But a reason we differentiate it from laser cellulite treatments is that it’s very, very low-level lasers — it’s not as invasive.For example, some therapies insert a tiny laser under the skin’s surface. As the laser fires, it breaks up fat cells, reducing the appearance of cellulite. But red light therapy is applied to the skin’s surface — so there aren’t any needles, and nothing goes inside the body.</p></div></div></div></div></div><div data-section-id="pf-de5f" data-pf-type="Section" class="sc-fmciRz bheIgq pf-215_"><div style="--cw:1170px" class="sc-gjNHFA gwWIgj"><div class="sc-ezbkAF A-dmbO pf-216_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-to-section="pf-de5f" data-offset="{&quot;all&quot;:50,&quot;laptop&quot;:50,&quot;tablet&quot;:50,&quot;mobile&quot;:50}" href="#" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c pf-hide" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:6;--c-md:6;--c-lg:4"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-gUQvok iVVDxu pf-217_ pf-hide"></div></div><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:6;--c-md:6;--c-lg:8"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-gUQvok iVVDxu pf-218_"><h2 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-cTAqQK eHolsa pf-219_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-jKTccl dCeBIC pf-221_">How to Perform Red Light Therapy for Cellulite Reduction</span></h2><p class="sc-bBHHxi fhourC pf-222_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Red light therapy uses LED lights that penetrate the skin’s surface, boosting blood flow. Increased circulation helps break up fat cells (i.e. cellulite), and stimulates collagen production at the same time. This leads to skin that’s smoother, firmer, and more youthful in appearance.In many cases, red light therapy is a service provided in medical spas. However, some companies make red light products that are meant for in-home use.We recommend researching clinics and companies thoroughly before investing in red light therapy services. Always consult with your doctor before changing your health routine or engaging in new self-care practices.</p></div></div></div></div></div><div data-section-id="pf-d244" data-pf-type="Section" class="sc-fmciRz bheIgq pf-224_"><div style="--cw:1170px" class="sc-gjNHFA gwWIgj"><div class="sc-ezbkAF A-dmbO pf-225_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-to-section="pf-d244" data-offset="{&quot;all&quot;:50,&quot;laptop&quot;:50,&quot;tablet&quot;:50,&quot;mobile&quot;:50}" href="#" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c pf-hide" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:6;--c-md:6;--c-lg:4"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-gUQvok iVVDxu pf-226_ pf-hide"></div></div><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:6;--c-md:6;--c-lg:8"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-gUQvok iVVDxu pf-227_"><h2 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-cTAqQK eHolsa pf-228_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-jKTccl dCeBIC pf-230_">FAQs: What people ask about Red Light Therapy</span></h2><p class="sc-bBHHxi fhourC pf-231_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Want to know more about red light therapy and how it works? We’ve got you covered with these red light therapy FAQs.</p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-cTAqQK eHolsa pf-233_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-jKTccl dCeBIC pf-235_">Can red light therapy completely get rid of cellulite?</span></h3><p class="sc-bBHHxi fhourC pf-236_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Yes and no. Red light therapy may help reduce cellulite, especially when used in combination with other treatments. Eating a balanced diet, exercising, and anti-cellulite creams may help boost the effects of red light therapy (or vice versa).</p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-cTAqQK eHolsa pf-238_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-jKTccl dCeBIC pf-240_">How long does it take to see results from red light therapy for cellulite?</span></h3><p class="sc-bBHHxi fhourC pf-241_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Everyone is different. Some people may achieve the results they want in four weeks, others in six weeks, others in ten weeks. This comes down to the results you want, whether you exercise, what you eat, and how often you get red light therapy.</p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-cTAqQK eHolsa pf-243_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-jKTccl dCeBIC pf-245_">Are there any side effects of red light therapy for cellulite?</span></h3><p class="sc-bBHHxi fhourC pf-246_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Red light therapy may result in burning, itching, redness, and stinging sensations. Some people may also experience allergic reactions and skin irritation after the treatment.Consult with your doctor before getting red light therapy to find out whether it’s a safe and effective choice for you.</p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-cTAqQK eHolsa pf-248_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-jKTccl dCeBIC pf-250_">How often should I do red light therapy for cellulite reduction?</span></h3><p class="sc-bBHHxi fhourC pf-251_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Some people choose to use their at-home red light therapy devices every day for ten to twenty minutes at a time. Other people visit medical spas for targeted treatments.The answer to this depends on your body, your goals, and how well you respond to red light therapy. Check with your doctor before getting red light therapy to find out what’s best for you.</p><div class="sc-ezbkAF A-dmbO pf-253_ pf-r pf-r-eh pf-hide" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"></div></div></div></div></div></div><div data-section-id=